derivation.yuyuan_name: Middle English: from Old French presumptueux, from late Latin praesumptuosus, variant of praesumptiosus 'full of boldness', from praesumptio (see presumption)

entry.tran: 放肆的；冒昧的；自作主张的
entry.def: If you describe someone or their behaviour as presumptuous, you disapprove of them because they are doing something that they have no right or authority to do.
